This pilot clinical trial studies KeraStat Skin Therapy in treating radiation dermatitis in patients with newly diagnosed stage 0-IIIA breast cancer.

 Radiation dermatitis is an itchy, painful skin rash that can occur following treatment with radiation.

 KeraStat Skin Therapy may be a better treatment for radiation dermatitis.

